{Speech 21 Answer 20}{}{Center}
{Speech 22}{}{- Who are you?\n- Me? And who are you? \n- I asked first. What's it to you, huh?\n- I couldn't care less, first or second, I don't know you and don't want to!\nThat's how charmingly you chatted with the man in the black leather jacket with a torn-off sleeve.@@- What's your name, drifter? - asked the guy in the leather jacket. - My name is none of your business, - you said curtly, as if cutting him off.@@The guy with a nasty grin on his face nods at you:\n- Aaah, a customer. Gonna buy some Jet?\n- No, thanks. I'm broke. - you answered and decided to get away from this criminal character.}
{Speech 22 Answer 44}{}{Call the child over to you.}
