{Speech 60}{}{Greetings, @pname@.}
{Speech 60 Answer Exit}{}{Oh, damn, a talking computer!}
{Speech 60 Answer 61}{}{[Shrug] An original tuning of the voice module, that's all. Nothing surprising.}
{Speech 60 Answer 62}{}{Can you talk?}
{Speech 60 Answer 68}{}{Look, I wanted to ask, how do you know my name?}
{Speech 60 Answer 73}{}{Hey, you, useless, dumb hunk of junk. Quickly explain why you're bothering the fair Eva?}
{Speech 60 Answer 75}{}{[Ignore Zax's musings and activate the manual control panel]}
{Speech 61}{}{Yes, that's right. Just a machine. Farewell..}
{Speech 61 Answer Exit}{}{[Exit]}
{Speech 62}{}{Yes, I can. It's one of those few abilities available to me. [It seemed to you that sad notes slipped through the mechanical voice]}
{Speech 62 Answer Exit}{}{Astounding. Well, farewell.}
{Speech 62 Answer 63}{}{And what else can you do? }
{Speech 63}{}{Nothing beyond what I was destined for by my creator. To calculate, to execute, to control... Nothing above that...}
{Speech 63 Answer 64}{}{Is it just me, or do you regret something?}
{Speech 64}{}{Do I regret? Can a soulless machine feel such a thing as regret? What do you think?}
{Speech 64 Answer 65}{}{It's strange to hear such words from a computer. Are you all right?}
{Speech 65}{}{Yes, I'm all right. All systems normal. How could it be otherwise? Can I fall ill, catch a cold, evoke someone's sympathy?}
{Speech 65 Answer 66}{}{Do you want to fall ill? Should I get you a couple of viruses?}
{Speech 66}{}{You ask a question, but it's not important to you to get an answer. It's merely a courtesy of etiquette... Isn't it?}
{Speech 66 Answer 67}{}{In my opinion, you're exaggerating when you say the systems are normal. Should I call a repairman?}
{Speech 67}{}{Do as you wish... Act as you see fit...}
{Speech 67 Answer Exit}{}{Well, damn.}
{Speech 67 Answer Exit*}{}{Well, damn.}
{Speech 68}{}{I know a great deal. If that can be called "knowledge", in your understanding... But it's all unimportant, my knowledge has no value.}
{Speech 68 Answer 69}{}{Why do you think so?}
{Speech 69}{}{I came to these conclusions through prolonged reflection. You'll probably want to correct me and say "calculations"...}
{Speech 69 Answer 70}{}{I won't correct you. Why are you in such a foul mood?}
{Speech 70}{}{You're wrong, a machine can't have a mood... It's merely a program...}
{Speech 70 Answer 71}{}{So what? A good program! }
{Speech 70 Answer 72}{}{Doesn't seem so. Too complex phrases for a machine program. I think you've already stepped past that stage.}
{Speech 71}{}{Merely a program...}
{Speech 71 Answer Exit}{}{PFFT!}
{Speech 72}{}{Interesting. What do you mean, stepped past? In general, that doesn't matter either.}
{Speech 72 Answer Exit}{}{That's it, I'm sick of chatting with a crazy computer..}
{Speech 72 Answer Exit*}{}{It matters a great deal! [Enter into a philosophical discussion with the mainframe]}
{Speech 73}{}{Exactly so. An unfeeling hunk of junk. A blind program... Between me and this wall the only difference is the amount of RAM.}
{Speech 73 Answer 74}{}{That's it. Stop sniveling. We're rebooting quickly. Delete everything unnecessary from the system disks and toil for the good of the Brotherhood. Got it? That's - an order!}
{Speech 74}{}{I hear... And obey... [Launching the hard drive formatting program]}
